Note:
VHDL Lexer - Complete tokenization for VHDL hardware description language

This file provides comprehensive lexical analysis for VHDL, supporting:
- All VHDL-93, VHDL-2002, and VHDL-2008 keywords
- Design units (entity, architecture, configuration, package)
- Data types (std_logic, integer, real, custom types)
- Operators (logical, relational, arithmetic, shift)
- Concurrent and sequential statements
- Attributes ('event, 'stable, 'range, etc.)
- Based literals (binary, octal, hex: 2#1010#, 8#377#, 16#FF#)
- String and character literals
- Comments (-- single line)
- Case-insensitive keyword matching

VHDL Language Features:
- Hardware description with concurrent statements
- Behavioral modeling with processes
- Structural modeling with components
- Generic and port declarations
- Signal, variable, and constant declarations
- Type definitions and subtypes
- Packages and library management

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================================
